---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How HealthMaps handles your privacy: no accounts, no cookies, no tracking scripts, no personal information collected."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section>
    <div class="max-w-[720px] mx-auto px-4 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-12 md:pb-16">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-body font-semibold mb-3">Site policy</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-[2.5rem] font-bold text-heading mb-5 tracking-[-0.01em] leading-tight">Privacy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-body leading-relaxed max-w-[36rem]">
        The short version: we don't collect personal information about you, and there are no tracking
        cookies on this site.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-paper-cream">
    <div class="max-w-[720px] mx-auto px-4 py-16 md:py-20 space-y-14 md:space-y-16">
      <!-- REVIEW: AI-drafted — confirm each claim matches reality before launch (especially the analytics section) -->
      <aside class="rounded-xl bg-bg-light p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-xs text-body mb-3 font-semibold">At a glance</p>
        <!-- REVIEW: confirm each at-a-glance row matches the prose below -->
        <dl class="divide-y divide-border text-sm">
          <div class="py-3 flex justify-between gap-6">
            <dt class="text-body">Accounts or sign-up forms</dt>
            <dd class="font-semibold text-heading text-right">None</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-3 flex justify-between gap-6">
            <dt class="text-body">Cookies</dt>
            <dd class="font-semibold text-heading text-right">None</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-3 flex justify-between gap-6">
            <dt class="text-body">Tracking scripts</dt>
            <dd class="font-semibold text-heading text-right">None</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-3 flex justify-between gap-6">
            <dt class="text-body">Analytics</dt>
            <dd class="font-semibold text-heading text-right">Aggregate server logs (Netlify)</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-3 flex justify-between gap-6">
            <dt class="text-body">Your email, if you write to us</dt>
            <dd class="font-semibold text-heading text-right">Used only to reply</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading mb-4">What we collect</h2>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
          HealthMaps is a simple information website. There are no accounts, no sign-up forms, and
          nothing you type into the site (like the cost calculator) is sent or stored anywhere — it
          runs entirely in your browser.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
          We use server-side analytics provided by our hosting service (Netlify) to see aggregate
          numbers — how many people visit and which pages they read. This works from standard server
          logs, places no cookies in your browser, runs no tracking scripts, and doesn't build a profile
          of you. We can't identify individual visitors and don't try to.
          <!-- REVIEW: confirm Netlify Analytics is what the $9/month covers; if you're not using it, simplify this paragraph -->
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="divide-y divide-border border-t border-border">
        <div class="py-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-heading mb-3">Cookies</h2>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            This site doesn't set cookies. That's also why you don't see a cookie banner.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="py-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-heading mb-3">If you email us</h2>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            If you contact us by email, we'll see your email address and whatever you choose to tell us.
            We use it only to reply, we don't add you to any list, and we don't share it with anyone.
            Given the subject matter of this site, please share only what you're comfortable sharing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="py-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-heading mb-3">Where the site is hosted</h2>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            The site is hosted by <a href="https://www.netlify.com/" class="text-primary font-semibold underline underline-offset-2" rel="noopener">Netlify</a>,
            whose servers may be located outside Australia. Like any web host, Netlify's infrastructure
            processes standard technical data (such as IP addresses) to deliver pages to your browser.
            See <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" class="text-primary font-semibold underline underline-offset-2" rel="noopener">Netlify's privacy policy</a> for details.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="py-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-heading mb-3">External links</h2>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            We link to external services (like Services Australia and crisis support lines). Those sites
            have their own privacy practices, which we don't control.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-10 border-t border-border">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading mb-4">Questions</h2>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
          This policy reflects how the site works as of June 2026. If the site changes in a way that
          affects privacy — for example, adding a feedback form — this page will be updated first.
          Questions about privacy: email
          <a href="mailto:jethrohedstrom@gmail.com" class="text-primary font-semibold underline underline-offset-2">jethrohedstrom@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
